# Java OOP Project â€“ Library Management System

## Description
A simple console-based Java project using OOP principles:
- Add books to library
- Issue and return books
- View book status (Available/Issued)

##  Technologies
- Java
- OOP: Inheritance, Encapsulation, Abstraction

## How to Run
1. Compile:
   javac Main.java
2. Run:
   java Main

## OOP Concepts Used
- `Book`, `User`, and `Library` are classes (abstraction)
- Book has fields `private` with getters/setters (encapsulation)
- Methods like `issueBook`, `returnBook` (polymorphism usage)

## Features
- Add and manage books
- Issue or return by book ID
